This executive order, issued by President Donald Trump on June 21, 2017, amends Executive Order 13597 by deleting subsection (b)(ii) of section 2. The order also requires the Secretaries of State and Homeland Security to revise the implementation plan described in section 2(b) of Executive Order 13597, in consultation with other executive departments and agencies. The order states that it does not impair the authority granted by law to executive departments or agencies, and it must be implemented consistent with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations. Additionally, the order does not create any right or benefit that can be legally enforced against the United States or any other entity.